  "title": "Senior Facilities Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Office/EAST/ Office Hours</strong><br /><strong>5 Days</strong><br /><strong>AWS + VB</strong><br /><br /><u><strong>JOB RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></u></p><ul><li>Manages the plant upgrading/expansion projects to ensure projects on schedule and within\nbudget, complies with regulatory and technical requirements.</li><li>Manages a team of engineer, technician and contractors to perform preventive maintenance activities, repair/breakdown maintenance, building and ground services to achieve minimum disruptions to operations and meet regulatory requirement and service standard.</li><li>Monitor utility capacity utilization and plan for future expansion to meet the growing utilities and facility needs.</li><li>Monitor and drive the department goals that were set.</li><li>Ensure critical system are built and operated in conformance to regulatory standard, system\n     specification and SOP.</li><li>Implement lean energy program and drive to improve energy efficiency.</li><li>Responsible for compliance to environmental and safety procedure and requirement.</li><li>Perform other tasks as assigned by the supervisor.</li></ul><p><u><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma in either Facility Engineering or Project Management.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant working experience</li><li>Desired Knowledge: (1)Compressed Air Systems  (2) Cleanroom system (3) Aircon systems or other\nplant facilities equipment maintenance & (4) Operating knowledge in a manufacturing environment.</li><li>In charge of 3 buildings in the East area</li><li>Able to commence work in short notice</li></ul><p>Interested Parties please WhatsApp us at <strong>88933424</strong> (Jasmine), and email your latest resume in WORD format to <strong>jl@businessedge.com.sg. </strong>You may call 65698233 for a private & confidential discussion. Look forward to hear from you too! </p><p></p><p></p>",
